metadata.name: BLOTTER #23
metadata.description:
Generative project that combines the creation of visual elements using artificial intelligence and digital collage.
It contains 101 pngs with transparency distributed in 8 different layers, which enables it to generate more than 222 million possible combinations.

metadata.name: Gonzion #121
metadata.description:
Gonzion is a Non-Linear Iterated Function System rendered using a method similar to Fractal Flames of Electric Sheep fame.

Technological tendrils from beyond light-aeons draw ancient crystals, transmuted fungus, sentient sigils in fossilized dimensions and alien topologies.

It's not built to run on a (2022) mobile phone and has been known to crash some, but runs fine on others.

For higher resolution renders add "#N" to the URL, default N=2.

metadata.name: ARAUCO #54
metadata.description:
The Araucaria Araucana, also known as pewén, is a sacred tree for the Mapuche and an emblem of Chile. With an origin dating back 260 million years to the Triassic period, it is part of the oldest forests on the planet. These ancient trees are endangered due to logging, forest fires, and grazing.

ARAUCO is a tribute to araucarias and Mapuche iconography. Incorporating elements such as the Kultrung, the Wünelfe star, and the staggered cross Ngümin, the work displays a typical landscape of southern Chile with the Andes Mountains in the background and the native forest. 

–

Press 's' to export a 4960x7016 PNG file suitable for A2 printing at 300 dpi.

Made with p5js.

Patricio Isaías, September 2022

metadata.name: Dencity #907
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Portals #49
metadata.description:
Portals -  is a generative collection sending you into your Memories and dreams.

Our whole life consists of different memories, some of them good and some of them not, which is absolutely normal.
I think each of us sometimes dives into our memories and dreams to relive that moment again, maybe change something in it or even forget it forever ?
Each of the memories has its own color, atmosphere and mood, some memories are big, some are short.
You certainly noticed how some days and sometimes even minutes and seconds last unbearably long, as well as when the day flies by in the same breath and you do not even have time to notice how it passed.
Let Portals take you on a journey through your memories, and have more good memories.

Artwork by aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Grid Return #30
metadata.description:
With "Grid Return" (Sept. 2022), I revisit the conceptual territory of my genesis work, "Grid Meditations" (Jan. 2022).

The four tenets of the Grid that I proclaimed eight months ago still ring true for me today:

1. The grid is the ultimate tool of abstraction.

2. The grid rejects any imitation of depth.

3. The grid exposes the true nature of the canvas as a two-dimensional surface.

4. The grid both imposes order and allows for the legibility of disorder.
